data.title: Yummy bakery!
data.text: Unfortunately (or maybe it's a good thing) this bakery isn't convenient to my house. It's in Historic Downtown Plano and has limited hours (wish it was open in the evening or on a Sat. afternoon). Baked goods are delicious. I bought cake slices, cupcakes and a cookie--it all had a really good homemade taste. Lots of choices, lots of flavors. Bake Rejoice lost a star because it wasn't very welcoming. No "glad you're here" or "thank you for coming." My questions were answered, and that was it.

data.title: Different idea
data.text: Starbucks is expensive, but the coffee is good.  I have found that a great birthday present is a gift card from Starbucks along with a card.  It shows you care and gives a friend, neighbor, kin person a great quick treat.

data.title: Good cake
data.text: We ordered a cake almond cake with pineapple filling. It was delicious and very dense. Also purchased a peanut butter cookie that was excellent. The only downside is you have to preorder the cake at least a week in advance. They usually have a cake they sell by the slice.
